snippet.textDisplay:
The Van Dijk "foul" on Reese James was ridiculous. He wasn't tugging or hugging the lad; he merely stood next to him and quite gently obstructed him with his body. It's all the more clear when James easily breaks away from VD's marking. Had VD really been hugging him, his hands would have tugged at his jersey, or toppled James. Even James didn't seem to protest, because it was a physical battle.
Football has become so strict in its officiating, that it seems that in the near future, footballers will have to defend and attack by social distancing themselves from their opponents. Terrible officiating.
